    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Yeah we do! There's an existing liveness endpoint that our doppelganger detection uses, so implementing the standard API should just be a straight-forward port of that: https://lighthouse-book.sigmaprime.io/api-lighthouse.html#lighthouseliveness.\r\n\r\nDeciding how to handle it in the VC is slightly more complicated. We could switch to the standard endpoint as soon as it's available, but this would break compatibility with older versions of the Lighthouse BN. Alternatively we could wait a release or two before switching over the VC. I think I prefer switching immediately, as most users will update VC+BN together anyway.",
